cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of vehicle re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed approach involves metric learning, which is a common technique in machine learning, particularly in deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of constraints during training, which is a common technique in optimization and constraint programming, falling under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve two benchmarks, which suggests the use of datasets, and hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with vehicle re-identification, which is a security-related application, and hence, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible sub-category.
